com.thomsonreuters.ema.access

Interface SeriesEntry


  • public interface SeriesEntry
    SeriesEntry represents an entry of Series.

    SeriesEntry associates entry's data and its data type.

    Code snippet: 
     void decode(Series series)
 {
    for(SeriesEntry seriesEntry : series)
    {
       System.out.println(" DataType: " + DataType.asString(seriesEntry.loadType()) + " Value: ");

       switch(seriesEntry.loadType())
       {
       case DataTypes.FIELD_LIST:
           decode(seriesEntry.fieldList());     
           break;
           
       ...
       
       }
    }
 }
    Objects of this class are intended to be short lived or rather transitional. This class is designed to efficiently perform setting and extracting of Map and its content. Objects of this class are not cache-able.
    See Also:
    Data, ComplexType, ReqMsg, RefreshMsg, UpdateMsg, StatusMsg, GenericMsg, PostMsg, AckMsg, FieldList, ElementList, Map, Vector, Series, FilterList, OmmOpaque, OmmXml, OmmAnsiPage, OmmError
